			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">The &amp;quot;request_id&amp;quot; field is included in every SRPC request and reply message.  It is intended to be used as a serial number for matching up requests and replies.  It is checked in NaClSrpcReceiveAndDispatch().

However, &amp;quot;request_id&amp;quot; is filled out from &amp;quot;next_outgoing_request_id&amp;quot;, and &amp;quot;next_outgoing_request_id&amp;quot; is never incremented, so &amp;quot;request_id&amp;quot; is always zero.

This is not a problem for any current users of SRPC.  This is currently just an implementation oddity.

This might be an interoperability problem for future users of SRPC if asynchronous, interleaved SRPC invocations are ever introduced.
